    I-perm-005 (#1199) slice 1: claim_labeler keystone — per-claim confidence bucket (pure) — Codex APPROVE iter1
    
    PURE, INERT (no production caller yet -> zero behavior change). Under the always-release reframe a
    non-VERIFIED claim is KEPT and LABELED instead of DELETED by the 4-role redactor; this is the
    deterministic Decision-B core.
    
    `claim_labeler.py`:
    - `confidence_bucket(*, is_verified, credibility, origin_count, has_cited_evidence) -> high |
      moderate | low | no-source-found`. REUSES `synthesis.disclosure_population._certainty_label`
      verbatim for the high/moderate/low thresholds (one source of truth, no drift) + adds the 4th
      `no-source-found` bucket (zero resolvable cited evidence — a first-class DISPLAYED outcome).
    - `render_confidence_marker(bucket)` — inline marker; `low`/`no-source-found` wording is unmistakable
      ("NOT confirmed by the cited source"/"shown unverified"); unknown bucket fails safe to low.
    - `is_asserted_as_fact(bucket)` — True only for high/moderate.
    
    §-1.1 invariant: a non-VERIFIED claim can NEVER be `high` (shared thresholds return `low` for
    is_verified=False); unknown credibility -> `low`. Pure — no LLM/IO, never re-runs a verifier.
    
    Codex APPROVE iter1 (zero P0/P1). The one P2 (autouse fixture used os.environ.pop -> env leak) is
    fixed: the fixture now uses monkeypatch.delenv(..., raising=False) which restores the prior env.
    
    Tests (6): no-cited-evidence -> no-source-found; non-verified never high; verified-high requires
    credibility AND >=2 origins; unknown-cred -> low; marker unmistakable + fail-safe; bucket matches the
    shared disclosure thresholds.
    
    Next slice: `annotate_report_against_verdicts` (keep+label, replacing the redactor DELETE under
    PG_ALWAYS_RELEASE) + the report.md render + claim_confidence.json + the UI chip.
    
